annotation.TEXT: BARF!

Now, I didn't realize this last time I played this level, but as you just saw in DP2, these cloud platforms can be stood on, so if you don't have a cape, you can still reach the secret exit, if you can get past the boos! Also, this message here is still unchanged.
Could I get enough height to reach it by bouncing off this Buzzy without Yoshi?
Double gulp!
D'oh! The sprite limit kept him from appearing that time!
Alright, there we go!
Well, no disco for you, I guess. So, I think there's a row of three 1F0 tiles there, for whatever reason. Are there any invisible 1F0 tiles over the other Deadly Acid of Death (TM) pits here?
Holy crackers, I got it! Whoo-hoo!
Goal tape average so far: 384 / 8 = 48 stars each.
Alright, DP1's done. (Also, off camera, I checked the second side area, with the cape feather and rows of coins in the sky, and I didn't see any changes there either.)
Now, can I pull off a miracle again and get yet another 50 to keep my average above 50?
Oh! This level has a total of six Fudge Stripe Cookies! Nice!
No Yoshis because they're scared of floating upside-down green ghost fire plants.
Goal tape average so far: 254 / 5 = 50.8 stars each.

Nope. Maybe it's possible by luring a Swooper from earlier in the level over here, but whatever. It's a bonus item anyway, so it's not like being unable to grab it would make the level unwinnable. I'll just Yoshi jump for it now.
Alright, since there's no red shells around here, I'll absolutely need to get a 50 here to keep my average above 50.
Doesn't look like it. Well, let's see what interesting patterns I can make with this control coin...
No Yoshis because they're being punished for eating Bananas without a license.
Huh, it looks like there's actually more than one 1F0 tile there.
Only 12 coins from that block? Darned cape making me glide down after each jump... If I'd switched to my flower, I would've scored more.
Hello, and welcome back to ludicrous speed! WHEEEE!!! Actually, this is Super Tweak World, and DP1 didn't seem to have had any changes made to it, so I'm speeding through it here.
If I can fly up there and stomp or thwack the guy, I can show this better.
Alright, now for the secret exit...
Now, it's nice to see that this pit has been filled with stuff, although there's a little bit of a blind jump since you can't immediately see the lowest cloud under the pipe here.

Ah, yep. The moon reappeared, which means it was inserted as a Map16 tile, instead of as an extended object, so instead of being a one-time-only collectible, it reappears every time I replay the level. (And, since it's a duplicate moon, the moon counter doesn't increase.)
Goal tape average so far: 344 / 7 = 49.143 stars each.

GAAAMMMEEE!!! Stupid rogue baseball coming from the left! One of the earlier Chucks must've thrown it, and for whatever reason, baseballs don't despawn off the side of the screen that they're coming from.
If you open all of these 1-up blocks at once, one of the 1-ups will turn invisible, but it's still there and collectible, so I'll still gain 4 lives here.
Whoops! I'm okay!
To be continued... Yo!
Careful! Ah, but at least this level seems to be set to "Vertical scroll at will" now, so I can properly see the stuff above me now!
I want my cape back, so I'm going to make a quick stop in Top Banana Zone here.
WAH!!! ...LOL at the Spike Top that I screwed up there!

That was weird. I didn't jump before colliding with that flashing Super Koopa there, but I still stomped him. The game sometimes lets you do that with certain enemies while you're on Yoshi for some reason.
Oh, I saw the camera pan up briefly at the start there!
MOOOOOONNNNN!!!!! Wow, way to use the camera as a hint, waffledoctor87! (Even if you didn't intentionally do that.)
Well, my average is still above 50, but one more sub-50 hit, and it'll drop below 50 (unless I get another glitched goal tape hit that's worth at least 46).
Bonus game average so far: 22 / 3 = 7.333 1-ups each.
Ugh! I didn't think that Boo would hit me there! Okay, I want to show this, so I'm Start+Selecting out and getting another feather from Top Banana Zone.
And, I'm back to normal speed again here while I clear the level.
Alright, now for the secret exit...
Doesn't look like it, although it's possible I just missed them. Well, whatever. I've wasted enough time here. Let's move on.
And... This area is still unchanged. Maybe you should tweak this area a bit, waffledoctor87.
Alright, I'm outta here.
Woo, I love how fast that river forms! ...And, Donut Plains 3's level dot is still missing.
Maybe I should've gotten two feathers, in case I take another hit somehow.
Whoa, watch out for the Boo Beams.
No Yoshis because they're too busy eating bananas right now.
50-star goal tape hits: 2 Goal tape average so far: 304 / 6 = 50.667 stars each.
Ah, so the NO blocks there were removed, and replaced with those clouds, which waffledoctor87 made "stand-on-able". (Normally, you can't stand on them.)
Well, that's a fail... Now I must hang my head in shame.
That unlocks Green Switch Palace. Now, there's just one more level that I want to do today... Donut House 1!
Slide-killing is less reliable when you're on Yoshi, especially when trying to slide uphill.
LOL, fail! I definitely did not intend for the control coin to end there!
И сега, нелепо скорост бонус игра!
Whoa! Okay, I'm still alive, but I think you can actually die there, so waffledoctor87, you should probably fix the screwed-up screen position in Top Banana Zone there.
I decided to return the footage to normal speed for a moment to show me tearing apart Conway's Game of Super Koopas there.
...Really! Of all the enemies I could've gotten hit by here, I let the most predictable and least mobile thing hit me, and it was something that I could've killed with a simple cape spin!
I'll just eat the Golden Swooper Football Pokey's top piece as I go up here!
Assuming I can stop getting beanballed for a moment...
Quintuple gulp! (Aw, I was hoping for a second there that that Swooper would get gulped up in that combo as well.)
Yeah, I used the turbo A button to get 32 coins there, which also had weird effects on the music's percussion during the process.
P-switch jump count: 2
Haha, well, at least Yoshi knows how to cheer me up by making a funny noise!
Alright, time for DP2! Let's see if anything's changed in this level...
There's more clouds here. Also, Yoshi's face was just "Podoboo-ized" for a moment there, but it's back to normal now, and the Podoboos stopped coming out of the lava anymore for some reason.

Oh, yeah. There's that yellow parakoopa that's jogging in place that I was wondering about last time, and as it turns out, waffledoctor87 simply placed it on top of dirt tile 1F0 here, which is actually invisible in a ghost house.
Double gulp!
...Assuming I can stop getting hit in silly ways...
Okay, I've gotta try to do this...
Have any changes been made to any other rooms in this level?
Now, thanks to the clouds, I could've easily taken the pipe leading to the secret exit. But, I'm going to stick to the normal route for now.

Well, it took a few episodes, but I'm now completely caught up to where I was in the previous version, which means, you guys can vote again! So, vote for either Donut Plains 3, Green Switch Palace, or Donut Secret to determine where I go next time!
Hmm... I wonder...
BARF!
BGM: Monopoly (NES) - Go to Jail
Umm... waffledoctor87, I think you should set this room to "Vertical scroll at will" since you made it possible to get up here without flying.

Nuts. Well, I considered myself really lucky to get that 50 last time. However, now I'll need a red shell (or a red Yoshi plus any shell) to glitch a goal tape in order to get the average back above 50.

Let's see if I can keep my average above 45 for the rest of this hack's playthrough at least. (If I get nothing but 40s from here on out, my average will stay above 45 until I hit my 13th goal, so I'll need a 50 or glitched >40 hit within the next five goals.)
Huh. There's a Fudge Stripe Cookie way up there. Now, I could easily Yoshi jump or fly to get it, but I'm wondering if it's possible to get without a Yoshi or cape.
Moon count: 3
